snippet.textDisplay:
Hey AJ. I wanna be honest here and say zi was a wee bit scathing towards u and ur team for how u lost at MSG on June 1st 2019 but Now! I want to say how impressed I was with how u boxed in the rematch. U were silky smooth on te night on DEC 7th 2019 and it will be remembered for being a brilliant and clever performance. U got caught a few times around te back of ur head and I saw Andy Ruiz was getting more and more frustrated 😤 as the rounds flew by. Massive respect my friend. I say my friend but I've never met u. I was a huge Mohammad Ali fan and Mike Tyson fan but now I will become a big fan of yours after the return bout with And Ruiz. I don't thi k anybody expected u to win so easily. U were triimmed down very well also. Thst was a major help I think. U showed great fee movement that I'd never seen from u before.
U kept circling away from his dangerous punches and it was a masterclass, and u deserve all the plaudits u get now AJ.
I hope u get the opportunity to fight and best that chump with the WBC belt. He was out of order and said some shitty things about u after ur loss and I hope one day soon u get to ram those words down his throat. Keep the great foot movement u have now bcos it will lead u to all out glory against Wilder 1dt and then u will have the tools to best even a classy operator in Tyson Fury..
All the very best for the year of 2020 too big man.. Take care and God bless.. Have a great Xmas and a, I was going to say prosperous New Year, but ur already well loaded man.. 😂

snippet.textDisplay: AJ some people are just born fighters and you are one of them therefore easier for upgrades. I think you are one of the fastest heavyweights out there BUT would be great to box even faster preparing for more dangerous opponents. Just like musicians can improve speed gradually go faster with the aid of metronome so can you in developing optimum speed. For a born fighter with the desire to WIN its more than possible to increase speed. Just for fun watch this movie called The Count of Monte Cristo if Im not mistaken. This guy always had fire in him but one of his flaws was swordsmanship however he learned the art of fencing from a Guru and improved his speed significantly and eventually he whipped the guy who beat him at sword fighting before. They say you are chinny...hell no ! BUT dont be complacent coz there are always guys who can hit harder avoiding to get hit is the best option but to develop a superfit body (not necessarily bulky n massive) with edequate nutrition and rest would make you stronger. I dunno bout the neck exercise thingy ? Does it do more good or harm ? You gotta use all tricks facing fighters like Wilder, fake a punch here and there to bait, element of surprise, swift ability to block, sway and move away from attacks, fast counters etc. thats why I recommend some martial arts principals like point of reference,  efficiency and positioning that would help you capitalise against opponents even when you are punching through somebody to the side however always be ready for a counter that extended punching arm shoulder touching cheek in defense however do not hang there too long or u'll get caught with an upper cut. In true martial arts stance u are always in defense even when you throw an attack. Good luck AJ may the force be with you :-D.
